<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 P 92/–: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Change in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Goold</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-25T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 25,
                                        1927—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Your 54, August 25, 11 a.m. The policy outlined in Department’s
                            telegram No. 20, April 26, 6 p.m., remains unchanged. This Government
                            cannot favor the flotation of any loan on the American market for the
                            benefit of a government which has not funded its American debt.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>